 2 oz of butter, vanilla, salt and reserved cooked half and half into mixing bowl and cook <b>6 min\/185°F\/speed 4<b>. Transfer half banana filling to bottom of cooled pie crust and spread out evenly. Place reserved banana slices on banana filling and top with remaining banana filling. Allow to cool slightly. Cover with cling wrap pressing directly onto the surface of the filling to avoid a \"skin\" from forming. Refrigerate while making pie topping. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","step":7},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pie Topping","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>.","step":8},{"isHeader":false,"content":" <b>Insert butterfly whisk.<b> Add whipping cream and vanilla into mixing bowl and without setting a time, whip at <b>speed 3<b> until desired stiffness is achieved, watching carefully to avoid overwhipping. <b>Remove butterfly whisk<b>. Place whipped cream on center of banana pie and spread out with spatula. Use the back of a spoon to make attractive swirls and peaks, then cover carefully with cling wrap and refrigerate 2-5 hours or until set.","step":9},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in banana slices. Weigh in orange juice and gently toss with bananas. Garnish pie with banana slices and serve immediately.","step":10}],"usefulItems":"rolling pin, cling wrap, parchment paper, baking weights, bowl, fine mesh sieve, wire rack, pie pan (approx. 9 in.), oven, refrigerator","id":"r160024","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-EahQeMjuLnQ\/XZWfdFYMrWI\/AAAAAAAAfE4\/f98G8GPyHuYV438khS915OfJvooUBC2IwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_vkWL7aMB9Ic8Hk6O.png","title":"Banana Cream Pie","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pie Crust"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 oz unsalted butter, chilled (cut into ¼ in. pieces), plus extra to grease"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 oz vegetable shortening, chilled (cut into ½ in. pieces)"},{"isHea